  <div class="container">
    <a href="/" class="logo">FlipSight</a>
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="last-updated">Last updated: February 28, 2026</p>

    <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
    <p>When you use FlipSight, we collect:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Account Information:</strong> Email address, username, and profile photo you provide during registration.</li>
      <li><strong>Usage Data:</strong> Items you scan, pricing lookups, deal scores, flip history, and app interaction patterns.</li>
      <li><strong>Device Information:</strong> Device type, operating system, and app version for compatibility and debugging.</li>
      <li><strong>Camera &amp; Photos:</strong> Images captured or selected for item identification are processed by AI and are not stored on our servers permanently.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
    <p>We use the collected information to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Provide item identification, pricing estimates, and deal analysis.</li>
      <li>Sync your data across devices.</li>
      <li>Generate leaderboard rankings and gamification features.</li>
      <li>Improve AI accuracy and app performance.</li>
      <li>Send deal alerts and notifications (with your permission).</li>
      <li>Process subscription purchases through RevenueCat.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. Data Storage &amp; Security</h2>
    <p>Your data is stored securely in cloud databases with encryption in transit. Local data is stored on your device using secure storage mechanisms. We implement industry-standard security practices to protect your information.</p>

    <h2>4. Third-Party Services</h2>
    <p>FlipSight uses the following third-party services:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>RevenueCat:</strong> Subscription and purchase management.</li>
      <li><strong>AI Services:</strong> Item identification and price estimation.</li>
      <li><strong>Expo:</strong> App infrastructure and push notifications.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Each service has its own privacy policy governing data handling.</p>

    <h2>5. Data Sharing</h2>
    <p>We do not sell your personal information. We may share anonymized, aggregated data for analytics purposes. Your username and flip statistics may appear on public leaderboards if you opt in.</p>

    <h2>6. Your Rights</h2>
    <p>You have the right to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Access your personal data.</li>
      <li>Request correction of inaccurate data.</li>
      <li>Delete your account and all associated data (available in Profile settings).</li>
      <li>Opt out of notifications at any time.</li>
      <li>Export your data upon request.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>7. Children's Privacy</h2>
    <p>FlipSight is not intended for children under 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If you believe a child has provided us with personal information, please contact us immediately.</p>

    <h2>8. Changes to This Policy</h2>
    <p>We may update this privacy policy periodically. We will notify you of significant changes through the app or via email. Continued use of FlipSight after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.</p>

    <h2>9. Contact Us</h2>
    <p>If you have questions about this privacy policy or your data, please contact us at:<br><a href="mailto:support@flipsight.app">support@flipsight.app</a></p>
